For **headless / one-shot** Claude Code runs (no interactive TTY session), follow **`.cursor/skills/claude-code-headless/SKILL.md`**.

From the repo root (so the working directory is the project), prefer:

```bash
./.cursor/claude-once.sh "Concrete task"
```

Do not suggest `--dangerously-skip-permissions` unless the user explicitly accepts the risk.

If **`claude-once.sh` exits 125** (rate limit), stderr lists **`wait_seconds`**. Do **not** retry `claude` / this script until that many seconds have elapsed — wait (`sleep`) or pause the workflow; do not loop tight retries.
